---
description: Rules when working with the ag-grid package (<AgGridReact />)
alwaysApply: false
---

IMPORTANT:

- ALWAYS provide a getRowId function to the <AgGridReact /> component.

  Example:

  ```tsx
  const getRowId = useCallback((params: GetRowIdParams) => {
    // Figure out how to get and stringify the id
    return params.data.cfop_id.toString();
  }, []);

  return (
    <AgGridReact
      // ... other props
      getRowId={getRowId}
    />
  );
  ```

- If the sable uses server side model, ALWAYS pass the prop "suppressServerSideFullWidthLoadingRow" so we can have a nice skeleton when loading

  Example:

  ```tsx
  return (
    <AgGridReact
      // ... Other props
      rowModelType="serverSide"
      suppressServerSideFullWidthLoadingRow
    />
  );
  ```
